description.narrative: Training for Pakistan (TFP) is a four-year, USAID-funded project that provides participant training services to USAID/Pakistan's sector teams. The project focus areas include Democracy and Governance, Education, Energy, Economic Growth and Health. The project delivers training that harnesses the full range of USAID participant training resources to contribute to the capacity development of partners across the Missions portfolio.
